# 🧠 OS Concept 1: CQRS (Command Query Responsibility Segregation)

## First Understand the Problem

Most applications use the same database for:

* Reading data
* Writing data

Example:

```text
Instagram
```

Millions of users read posts.

Very few users create posts.

Reads and writes have different needs.

---

## CQRS Solution

Separate:

### Command Side

Handles:

* Create
* Update
* Delete

(Writes)

---

### Query Side

Handles:

* Read operations

---

## Real-World Analogy

Library 📚

Writing side:

```text
Librarian updates books
```

Reading side:

```text
Students search books
```

Different tasks, different systems.

---

## Why Useful?

✔ Better scalability

✔ Faster reads

✔ Easier optimization

---

## Interview Question

**Q: Why use CQRS?**

👉 Because read and write workloads often have different performance requirements.

---

## Memory Trick

```text
Command = Change data
Query = Read data
```

---

# 🧠 OS Concept 2: Distributed Locking

🔥 Common backend interview topic.

---

## Problem

Multiple servers trying to modify same data.

Example:

```text
Last seat booking
```

Server A books it.

Server B books it.

Now two users have same seat. ❌

---

## Solution

Distributed Lock

Only one server gets permission.

Others wait.

---

## Real-World Analogy

Single washroom key 🔑

Only one person can enter at a time.

---

## Why Needed?

✔ Prevent data corruption

✔ Maintain consistency

---

## Popular Tool

Redis distributed locks

---

## Interview Question

**Q: Why distributed locking needed?**

👉 To prevent multiple systems from modifying shared resources simultaneously.

---

## Memory Trick

```text
One resource
One lock
```

---

# ⚙️ COA Concept 3: Heterogeneous Computing

🔥 Modern computing concept.

---

## Traditional System

Only CPU does computation.

---

## Modern System

Different processors do different work.

Example:

```text
CPU → control logic

GPU → parallel processing

TPU → AI computation
```

---

## Why?

Different hardware excels at different tasks.

---

## Real-World Analogy

Hospital 🏥

Different specialists:

* Surgeon
* Cardiologist
* Neurologist

Each does specific work.

---

## Benefits

✔ Better performance

✔ Better energy efficiency

✔ Faster execution

---

## Interview Question

**Q: What is heterogeneous computing?**

👉 Using different types of processors together for maximum efficiency.

---

## Memory Trick

```text
Right processor
For right task
```

---

# ⚙️ COA Concept 4: AI Runtime Systems

🔥 Important AI infrastructure concept.

---

## What Happens After Training?

Model must run efficiently.

That execution environment is:

👉 AI Runtime

---

## Responsibilities

### Load Model

```text
Load AI model into memory
```

---

### Execute Operations

Perform inference.

---

### Manage Hardware

Use:

* CPU
* GPU
* TPU

efficiently.

---

## Real-World Analogy

Movie player 🎬

Movie file exists.

Player actually runs it.

---

## Examples

* ONNX Runtime
* TensorRT

---

## Interview Question

**Q: Why AI runtime systems are important?**

👉 Because they execute trained models efficiently on available hardware.

---

## Memory Trick

```text
Model = file
Runtime = executor
```

